name: Biexponential
description: Performs a biexponential transformation of your data.

properties.name: a
properties.description: See the function description in the operator documentation. Defaults to 0.5.

properties.name: b
properties.description: See the function description in the operator documentation. Defaults to 1.0.

properties.name: c
properties.description: See the function description in the operator documentation. Defaults to 0.5.

properties.name: d
properties.description: See the function description in the operator documentation. Defaults to 1.0.

properties.name: f
properties.description: A constant bias for the intercept. Defaults to 0.

properties.name: w
properties.description: A constant bias for the 0 point of the data. Defaults to 0.
